article.headline: Denver 84, Colorado State 67
article.story: DENVER (AP) -- Zeljko Zupic had 21 points and 10 rebounds to lead Denver to its first victory over Colorado State in nearly 14 years, winning 84-67 Saturday. Brett Starkey added 18 points and 10 rebounds for Denver (4-3) to win for the fourth time in five games. The Pioneers hit 15-of-27 shots in the second half to end a nine-game losing streak to Colorado State. Matt Williams led Colorado State (4-4) with 18 points and nine rebounds. The Rams last lost to Denver on Jan. 6, 1979. The Pioneers used runs in the second half to decide the game. Starkey had seven points early in the second half in a 17-0 run to put Denver ahead 51-45 with 11:45 left. Colorado State was as close as 53-50 after a layup by Freddy Robinson with 10:13 remaining. After a jumper by Williams made it 58-54, Zupic scored four points of a 9-0 run that made it 67-54 with 5:50 left Williams came off the bench to score 12 points, including a layup in a 9-0 run late in the first half to put Colorado State ahead 37-28. Zupic's 3-pointer closed the gap to 39-32, but a layup by Morris put the Rams, which shot 58 percent, ahead 41-32 at the break.
